cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.NI 

This paper discusses the performance evaluation of distributed computing environments using Hadoop and Spark frameworks for processing Big Data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also deals with data management and analysis, which falls under cs.DB (Databases). The use of machine learning and Deep Learning applications suggests the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the problem of growing data generated by IoT and multimodal interaction channels, which can be categorized under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
